Title : Probota Monastery
Text : [[File:Mănăstirea Probota 20100721-156.JPG|thumb|The monastery church, dedicated to [[Saint Nicholas]]]]
'''Probota Monastery''' ({{lang-ro|Mănăstirea Probota}}) is a [[Romanian Orthodox]] monastery in Probota village, [[Dolhasca]] town, [[Suceava County]], [[Romania]]. Built in 1530, with [[Peter IV Rareș]] as ''[[ktitor]]'', it is one of eight buildings that make up the [[churches of Moldavia]] [[UNESCO World Heritage Site]],<ref>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/598 Churches of Moldavia] at the UNESCO site</ref> and is also listed as a [[Monument istoric|historic monument]] by the country's [[Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs (Romania)|Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs]].<ref>{{ro icon}} [http://www.patrimoniu.ro/images/LMI/LMI-2010_SV.pdf Lista Monumentelor Istorice 2010: Judeţul Suceava], p.2173</ref>

==Burials==
*[[Petru Rareș]]

